A South African National Defence Force (SANDF) patrol is seen in Eldorado Park. JOHANNESBURG - The National State of Disaster ends on Saturday and government is still to announce if there will be an extension. It has been five months since the coronavirus pandemic was declared a national disaster. READ: National State of Disaster extended until mid-July The first expiry date was 15 June and since then it's been extended every month as required by law. Meanwhile, several business organisations have started a nationwide campaign calling for an end to the COVID-19 lockdown. READ: Government declares coronavirus pandemic a national disaster They say it served its purpose and a further continuation will result in a humanitarian disaster. The steering committee of this campaign includes well-known economists Dawie Roodt and Mike Schussler. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.